{"abstract":[{"code":"GAsyncInitable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is an interface for asynchronously initializable objects."}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncInitable"},"relationshipsSections":[{"title":"Conforms To","kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncInitableProtocol","doc:\/\/GIO\/4GLib14PointerWrapperP"],"type":"conformsTo"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/asyncinitable"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"AsyncInitable","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This is the asynchronous version of [iface","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Initable","type":"reference"},{"text":"]; it behaves the same","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"in all ways except that initialization is asynchronous. For more details"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"see the descriptions on ","type":"text"},{"code":"GInitable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A class may implement both the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GInitable"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"GAsyncInitable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" interfaces."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Users of objects implementing this are not intended to use the interface","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"method directly; instead it will be used automatically in various ways."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For C applications you generally just call [func"},{"code":"Gio.AsyncInitable.new_async","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"directly, or indirectly via a ","type":"text"},{"code":"foo_thing_new_async()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" wrapper. This will call","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.AsyncInitable.init_async"},{"type":"text","text":"] under the covers, calling back with "},{"code":"NULL","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and a set "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GError"},{"text":" on failure.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A typical implementation might look something like this:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"c","code":["enum {","   NOT_INITIALIZED,","   INITIALIZING,","   INITIALIZED","};","","static void","_foo_ready_cb (Foo *self)","{","  GList *l;","","  self->priv->state = INITIALIZED;","","  for (l = self->priv->init_results; l != NULL; l = l->next)","    {","      GTask *task = l->data;","","      if (self->priv->success)","        g_task_return_boolean (task, TRUE);","      else","        g_task_return_new_error (task, ...);","      g_object_unref (task);","    }","","  g_list_free (self->priv->init_results);","  self->priv->init_results = NULL;","}","","static void","foo_init_async (GAsyncInitable       *initable,","                int                   io_priority,","                GCancellable         *cancellable,","                GAsyncReadyCallback   callback,","                gpointer              user_data)","{","  Foo *self = FOO (initable);","  GTask *task;","","  task = g_task_new (initable, cancellable, callback, user_data);","  g_task_set_name (task, G_STRFUNC);","","  switch (self->priv->state)","    {","      case NOT_INITIALIZED:","        _foo_get_ready (self);","        self->priv->init_results = g_list_append (self->priv->init_results,","                                                  task);","        self->priv->state = INITIALIZING;","        break;","      case INITIALIZING:","        self->priv->init_results = g_list_append (self->priv->init_results,","                                                  task);","        break;","      case INITIALIZED:","        if (!self->priv->success)","          g_task_return_new_error (task, ...);","        else","          g_task_return_boolean (task, TRUE);","        g_object_unref (task);","        break;","    }","}","","static gboolean","foo_init_finish (GAsyncInitable       *initable,","                 GAsyncResult         *result,","                 GError              **error)","{","  g_return_val_if_fail (g_task_is_valid (result, initable), FALSE);","","  return g_task_propagate_boolean (G_TASK (result), error);","}","","static void","foo_async_initable_iface_init (gpointer g_iface,","                               gpointer data)","{","  GAsyncInitableIface *iface = g_iface;","","  iface->init_async = foo_init_async;","  iface->init_finish = foo_init_finish;","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncInitable"},{"type":"text","text":" type acts as an owner of an underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GAsyncInitable"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"It provides the methods that can operate on this data type through ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncInitableProtocol"},{"text":" conformance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncInitable"},{"type":"text","text":" as a strong reference or owner of a "},{"code":"GAsyncInitable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Note","content